# Drawing Layer Rules

## Architecture
The drawing system has three files:
1. **`drawing-layer.js`** — Core `DrawingLayer` class (SVG annotation engine)
2. **`drawing-integration.js`** — Toolbar UI, event wiring, auto-save
3. **`drawing-controls.css`** — Toolbar and drawing layer styles

## DrawingLayer Class (`drawing-layer.js`)

### Constructor
```javascript
const drawingLayer = new DrawingLayer(svgElement);
// svgElement = D3 selection of the main SVG
```

### SVG Group Structure
```
<g class="drawing-layer">        ← Master group (pointer-events toggled)
  <g class="drawing-paths">      ← Freehand pen strokes
  <g class="drawing-shapes">     ← Circles and rectangles
  <g class="drawing-text">       ← Text annotations
</g>
```

### Available Tools
| Tool | Element | Interaction |
|------|---------|-------------|
| `pen` | `<path>` | Click-drag to draw freehand |
| `circle` | `<circle>` | Click-drag to set center and radius |
| `rectangle` | `<rect>` | Click-drag to define corners |
| `text` | `<text>` | Click to place, prompt for text input |

### Key Properties
```javascript
this.drawingMode     // boolean: is drawing enabled?
this.currentTool     // 'pen' | 'circle' | 'rectangle' | 'text'
this.currentColor    // hex color string (default: '#ff0000')
this.currentStrokeWidth  // number (default: 2)
this.annotations     // array of annotation objects
this.history         // array of serialized states (max 50)
this.historyIndex    // current position in history
```

### Key Methods
```javascript
enableDrawing()          // Enable drawing mode, attach event listeners
disableDrawing()         // Disable drawing mode, remove listeners
setTool(tool)            // Change current drawing tool
setColor(color)          // Change current stroke/fill color
setStrokeWidth(width)    // Change current stroke width
undo()                   // Step back in history
redo()                   // Step forward in history
clearAll(saveToHistory)  // Remove all annotations
exportAnnotations()      // Returns JSON string of all annotations
importAnnotations(json)  // Load annotations from JSON string
saveToLocalStorage(key)  // Persist to localStorage
loadFromLocalStorage(key) // Restore from localStorage
```

### Annotation Object Format
```javascript
{
    type: 'path' | 'circle' | 'rectangle' | 'text',
    element: d3Selection,   // D3 selection (not serialized)
    data: 'M10,20L30,40',  // SVG path data (paths only)
    text: 'My note',       // Text content (text only)
    x: 100, y: 200,        // Position (text only)
    color: '#ff0000',
    strokeWidth: 2
}
```

### History System
- Max 50 history entries
- `saveToHistory()` serializes current annotations (strips D3 elements)
- `restoreFromHistory()` clears and recreates annotations from serialized data
- Undo/redo manipulate `historyIndex`

## Drawing Integration (`drawing-integration.js`)

### Initialization
```javascript
// Auto-initializes on DOMContentLoaded (2s delay) and window.load (1s delay)
// Waits for SVG element to be available
function initializeDrawingLayer() {
    const svg = window.svgElement || d3.select("#graph svg");
    drawingLayer = new DrawingLayer(svg);
    addDrawingToolbar();
    addToolbarToggle();
    drawingLayer.loadFromLocalStorage('sim4action-annotations');
}
```

### Auto-Save
Annotations are auto-saved every 30 seconds to localStorage.

### Global Functions (attached to window)
All toolbar functions are global for inline `onclick` handlers:
- `toggleDrawingMode()`, `toggleToolbarVisibility()`
- `selectTool(tool)`, `changeColor(color)`, `changeStrokeWidth(width)`
- `undoDrawing()`, `redoDrawing()`
- `saveAnnotations()`, `loadAnnotations()`, `clearAllDrawings()`
- `exportAnnotations()`, `importAnnotations()`

### LocalStorage Key
Currently hardcoded to `'sandbox-fishery-annotations'` (legacy naming). When making the drawing layer system-aware, change this to include the system ID:
```javascript
const storageKey = `sim4action-annotations-${systemId}`;
```

## CSS Structure (`drawing-controls.css`)

### Toolbar Positioning
```css
.drawing-toolbar {
    position: fixed;
    top: 20px;
    right: 20px;
    z-index: 1000;
}
.toolbar-toggle-btn {
    position: fixed;
    top: 20px;
    right: 240px;
    z-index: 1001;
}
```

### Responsive
At `max-width: 768px`:
- Toolbar goes full-width
- Tool buttons become 4-column grid
- Action buttons become 3-column grid

## Development Guidelines
1. **Drawing layer must be on top** of the D3 visualization but below UI modals
2. **Toggle pointer-events** to switch between drawing and graph interaction
3. **D3 event namespaces** are used (`.drawing`) to avoid conflicts: `svg.on('mousedown.drawing', ...)`
4. **Cursor changes** to `crosshair` when drawing is enabled
5. **Don't break zoom/pan** — drawing mode should fully capture mouse events when active
6. **Export/import uses JSON** — annotations can be shared between sessions
7. **History limit is 50** — prevents memory issues with many annotations
8. **Text uses `prompt()`** — consider replacing with an inline text input for better UX
